article.headline: Fordham 76, St. Francis (N.Y.) 49
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Marcus Stout scored 18 points to lead Fordham past St. Francis, N.Y., 76-49 Sunday, extending the Terriers' winless streak to six games. Bryant Dunston had 12 points and Sebastian Greene added 11 for the Rams (2-2), who led 31-22 at halftime. Greene's two free gave Fordham a 56-36 lead with 6:59 remaining. Jamaal Womack had 20 points and was the only scorer in double figures for the Terriers (0-6), who were outrebounded 46-23. Stout had five points, including a 3-pointer, to help put the Rams ahead 13-2. St. Francis twice closed within six points, the last at 26-20 on a layup by Womack with 2:48 left in the half.
